        <div type="translation" xml:lang="ndl" source="bib:Bosch1924_01">
          <!--masc2argr: reading the EGD, I have added the source - but perhaps it should be done in another tag rather than in the div? It also seems that in theory the English translation (which is also more recent), should come first. On the other hand, I am not sure whether the translation I have arrived at is more useful than Bosch'-->
<p>Heil! Śaka-jaren verloopen, in het Śaka jaar 1338. Aldus is het tijdstip, dat Zijne Hoogheid van Talonan in ontvangst <seg cert="low">nam de storting</seg> ten behoeve van den <foreign>bhaṭāra</foreign> van Paguhan, die overleden is te Pramalaya, ontvangen door de <supplied reason="explanation">ambtenaren</supplied> <foreign>aṅucap gave</foreign> in het huis Diṅgi<supplied reason="omitted" cert="low">ṅ</supplied>va, de <foreign>patih</foreign> Səmut, de <foreign>ārya</foreign> Pagəh, de <foreign>ārya</foreign> Guna, de <foreign>patih</foreign> van Paguhan, de <foreign>patih</foreign> Sirəg, de <foreign>patih</foreign> Tembeṅ, <supplied reason="explanation">zijn zij</supplied> die het geld ontvingen; de hoeveelheid van het geld is 200.000, twee honderd duizend, twee honderd duizend totaal; <supplied reason="explanation">op</supplied> Kaliwon, den 13den van de lichte maandhelft, in de maand Asuji. Zich noemende <sic>Sakavasa</sic>.</p>
        </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:masc">
 	<!--translation encoded as per EGD §9.2 -->
<!-- argr2masc: thoroughly read EGD 9.2, esp. on use of supplied instead of (...) and [...] -->
	<p>Hail! In the elapsed Śaka year 1338: such was the time that His Majesty of Talonan <seg cert="low">took over in
	    turn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>hanimbal</foreign></supplied></seg> the piece of land <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>varukira</foreign></supplied> of the Lord at Paguhan, he who was released in the
	    Highest Abode (or at Paramālaya). <supplied reason="explanation">The message</supplied> was received (<foreign>kataṅgap</foreign>) by "those who discuss the works"<!-- argr2masc: use <q> as per EGD 10.4/Quotations without an encoded reference  --> (<foreign>denira saṅ aṅucap gave</foreign>) at the (stone) building Didiva. The <foreign>patih</foreign> Səmut, the <foreign>arya pagəh</foreign> (the Venerable Pagəh), the <foreign>arya Guna</foreign> (the Venerable Guna), the <foreign>patih</foreign> at Paguhan (by the master at Paguhan), the <foreign>patih</foreign> Sərəg, the <foreign>patih</foreign> at Tembeṅ,
	    [those are] the people who received money. The amount of money: 200.000, two hundred
	    thousand, two hundred thousand in total <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gənəp</foreign></supplied>, on Kliwon<!-- argr2masc: I am hesitant about use of w here and for Kawasa below. --> (<foreign>kalivon</foreign>), the thirteenth <supplied reason="explanation">day</supplied> of the waxing fortnight, the month of Asuji, signed by (litt. “bearing the name”<!-- argr2masc: use <q> -->) <foreign>saṅ</foreign> Kavasa.</p>
         </div>
